dad Ju\u00e1rez]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2007 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup|2007 Mexico]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2008 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup|2008 Mexico]]|}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2005 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup|2005 Dominican Republic]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[South American Women's Volleyball Championship|South American Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2005 Women's South American Volleyball Championship|2005 La Paz]] |}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2007 Women's South American Volleyball Championship|2007 Santiago]] |}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2009 Women's South American Volleyball Championship|2009 Porto Alegre]] |}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2011 Women's South American Volleyball Championship|2011 Lima]] |}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2013 Women's South American Volleyball Championship|2013 Ica]] | }}\n{{MedalGold| [[2015 Women's South American Volleyball Championship|2015 Cartagena]] |}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2019 Women's South American Volleyball Championship|2019 Cajamarca]] |}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Final Four Women's Volleyball Cup|Final Four Cup]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2008 Final Four Women's Volleyball Cup|2008 Fortaleza]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2009 Final Four Women's Volleyball Cup|2009 Lima]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Montreux Volley Masters]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2005 Montreux Volley Masters|2005 Switzerland]] |}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2006 Montreux Volley Masters|2006 Switzerland]] |}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2009 Montreux Volley Masters|2009 Switzerland]] |}}\n}}\n\n'''Sheilla Tavares de Castro''' (born 1 July 1983 in [[Belo Horizonte]]) is a [[volleyball]] player from [[Brazil]], who represented her native country at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]], in [[Beijing]], [[China]], and in the [[2012 Summer Olympics]].  On both occasions the [[Brazil women's national volleyball team|Brazilian national team]] won the gold medal. She also played the [[2016 Summer Olympics]], when Brazil placed fifth.\n\n==Career==\nShe plays as opposite in the Brazilian national team, and in [[Osasco Voleibol Clube|Molico/Osasco]]. She made her debut for the national team against [[Colombia]].\n\nCastro was named \"Most Valuable Player\" at the [[2006 FIVB World Grand Prix]] in [[Reggio Calabria]], [[Italy]], and at the [[2009 FIVB World Grand Prix]] in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]], with Brazil winning the gold medal both times.\nAt the [[2011 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup|2011 Pan-American Cup]], Castro was given the \"Most Valuable Player\" award,<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.norceca.org/July%209-2011_Brazilian%20Sheilla%20Castro%20the%20MVP%20of%20the%20Pan%20Am%20Cup.htm|title=Brazilian Sheilla Castro the MVP of the Pan Am Cup|author=NORCECA|date=2011-07-09|accessdate=2011-07-09}}</ref> also winning the gold medal with her national team.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://voleysur.org/v1/noticias_esp.asp?id=2387|title=Copa Panamericana Femenina: Brasile\u00f1as son nuevas reinas|author=Confederaci\u00f3n Sudamericana de Voleibol|date=2011-07-10|accessdate=2011-07-10|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\nSheilla was part of the national team who won the gold medal at the [[Volleyball at the 2011 Pan American Games \u2013 Women's tournament|2011 Pan American Games]] held in [[Guadalajara]], [[Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=32693&Language=en|title=Brazil wins fourth Pan Am Games gold medal|author=FIVB|date=2011-10-20|accessdate=2011-10-20}}</ref>\n\nPlaying with [[Osasco Voleibol Clube|Sollys Nestl\u00e9 Osasco]], Castro won the gold medal and the \"Most Valuable Player\" and \"Best Scorer\" awards in the [[2012 FIVB Women's Club World Championship|2012 FIVB Club World Championship]] held in [[Doha]], [[Qatar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=37130&Language=en|title=Trentino Diatec and Sollys Nestle crowned in Doha|location=Doha, Qatar|author=FIVB|date=2012-10-19|accessdate=2012-10-19}}</ref>\n\nCastro won the \"Best Opposite\" award and the gold medal with her National Team in the [[2013 Women's South American Volleyball Championship|2013 South American Championship]] held in [[Ica, Peru]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.voleysur.org/v1/noticias_esp.asp?id=3111|title=SUDAMERICANO FEMENINO: Brasil, Argentina y Per\u00fa se consagraron los mejores del Continente|location=Ica, Peru|language=Spanish|publisher=CSV|date=2013-09-22|accessdate=2013-09-22}}</ref>\nCastro won the silver medal in the [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Women's Club World Championship|2014 FIVB Club World Championship]] after her club lost 0-3 to the Russian [[WVC Dynamo Kazan|Dinamo Kazan]] in the championship match.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=45651&Language=en|title=Russia's Kazan capture Women's Club World championship in style|publisher=FIVB|location=Zurich, Switzerland|date=2014-05-11|accessdate=2014-05-11}}</ref>\n\nCastro played with her national team,<ref>{{cite web|title=Team Roster \u2013 Brazil|url=http://italy2014.fivb.org/en/competition/teams/BRA-Brazil/team_roster|publisher=FIVB|accessdate=12 October 2014}}</ref> winning the bronze at the [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship|2014 World Championship]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=50092&Language=en|title=USA win first World Championship title, China and Brazil complete the podium|publisher=FIVB|location=Milan, Italy|date=12 October 2014|accessdate=12 October 2014}}</ref> when her team defeated Italy 3-2 in the bronze medal match.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://esporte.uol.com.br/volei/ultimas-noticias/2014/10/12/brasil-passa-sufoco-e-quase-toma-virada-mas-conquista-bronze-ante-italia.htm|title=Brasil passa sufoco e quase toma virada, mas conquista bronze ante It\u00e1lia|newspaper=UOL|last=Carneiro|first=Leandro|language=Portuguese|location=Milan, Italy|date=12 October 2014|accessdate=12 October 2014}}</ref>\nShe won the Best Opposite Spiker in the [[2016 FIVB Volleyball World Grand Prix#Awards|2016 FIVB World Grand Prix]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Brazil win record 11th title in World Grand Prix|url=http://worldgrandprix.2016.fivb.com/en/news/brazil-win-record-11th-title-in-world?id=63376|publisher=[[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Volleyball]]|accessdate=11 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nAfter finishig the [[2016 Olympic Games]] in 5th place, Castro annouced her retirement from the national team.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sheilla e Fabiana anunciam aposentadoria da sele\u00e7\u00e3o|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/esportes/sheilla-fabiana-anunciam-aposentadoria-da-selecao-19939100|publisher=O Globo|date=17 August 2016|accessdate=7 April 2020|language=Portuguese}}</ref> In 2019, without playing for three years even for clubs, she decided to return to the national team and played the [[2019 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Cup|2019 FIVB World Cup]] and the [[2019 Women's South American Volleyball Championship|2019 South American Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sele\u00e7\u00e3o feminina bate Col\u00f4mbia e leva Sul-Americano de V\u00f4lei pela 13\u00aa vez seguida|url=https://www.terra.com.br/esportes/volei/selecao-feminina-bate-colombia-e-leva-sul-americano-de-volei-pela-13-vez-seguida,daca7605b39ae49e06ae8cd48a38f1a13xhdh2zs.html|publisher=Terra|date=2 September 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020|language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Brasil vence a R\u00fassia e termina a Copa do Mundo feminina de v\u00f4lei em quarto lugar|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/esportes/brasil-vence-russia-termina-copa-do-mundo-feminina-de-volei-em-quarto-lugar-23983086|publisher=O Globo|date=29 September 2019|accessdate=7 April 2020|language=Portuguese}}</ref>  \n\n==Clubs==\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Mackenzie Esporte Clube]] (1997\u20132000)\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Minas T\u00eanis Clube (Volleyball)|MRV/Minas]] (2001\u20132004)\n*{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Robursport Volley Pesaro|Scavolini Pesaro]] (2004\u20132008)\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[S\u00e3o Caetano Esporte Clube|S\u00e3o Caetano/Blausiegel]] (2008\u20132010)\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Rio de Janeiro V\u00f4lei Clube|Unilever/Rio de Janeiro]] (2010\u20132012)\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Osasco Voleibol Clube|Molico Osasco]] (2012\u20132014)\n*{{flagicon|TUR}} [[Vak\u0131fbank Spor Kul\u00fcb\u00fc|Vak\u0131fbank Istanbul]] (2014\u20132016)\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Minas T\u00eanis Clube (Volleyball)|Minas T\u00eanis Clube]] (2019\u20132020)\n\n==Awards==\n\n===Individuals===\n* ''[[2005 FIVB Women's World Grand Champions Cup#Awards|2005 FIVB World Grand Champions Cup \u2013 \"Most Valuable Player\"]]''\n* ''[[2005 FIVB Women's World Grand Champions Cup#Awards|2005 FIVB World Grand Champions Cup \u2013 \"Best Scorer\"]]''\n* ''2005\u201306 CEV Cup \u2013 \"Best Spiker\"''\n* ''[[2006 FIVB World Grand Prix#Individual awards|2006 FIVB World Grand Prix \u2013 \"Most Valuable Player\"]]''\n* ''2008\u201309 Brazilian Superleague \u2013 \"Best Scorer\"''\n* ''2008\u201309 Brazilian Superleague \u2013 \"Best Spiker\"''\n* ''[[2009 FIVB World Grand Prix#Individual awards|2009 FIVB World Grand Prix \u2013 \"Most Valuable Player\"]]''\n* ''2009\u201310 Brazilian Superliga \u2013 \"Best Spiker\"''\n* ''2009\u201310 Brazilian Superliga \u2013 \"Best Server\"''\n* ''[[2011 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup#Individual awards|2011 Pan-American Cup \u2013 \"Most Valuable Player\"]]''\n* ''[[2011 Women's South American Volleyball Championship#Individual awards|2011 South American Championship \u2013 \"Most Valuable Player\"]]''\n* ''[[Volleyball at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's tournament#Individual awards|2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 \"Best Server\"]]''\n* ''[[2012 Women's South American Volleyball Club Championship#Individual awards|2012 South American Club Championship \u2013 \"Most Valuable Player\"]]''\n* ''[[2012 FIVB Women's Club World Championship#Awards|2012 FIVB Club World Championship \u2013 \"Best Most Valuable Player\"]]''\n* ''[[2012 FIVB Women's Club World Championship#Awards|2012 FIVB Club World Championship \u2013 \"Best Scorer\"]]''\n* ''[[2013 Women's South American Volleyball Championship#All-Star team|2013 South American Championship \u2013 \"Best\nOpposite Spiker\"]]''\n* ''[[2014 FIVB World Grand Prix#Awards|2014 FIVB World Grand Prix \u2013 \"Best Opposite Spiker\"]]''\n* ''[[2014 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship#Awards|2014 FIVB World Championship \u2013 \"Best Opposite Spiker\"]]''\n* ''[[2016 FIVB Volleyball World Grand Prix#Awards|2016 FIVB World Grand Prix \u2013 \"Best Outside Spiker\"]]''\n\n===Clubs===\n\n* 2001\u201302 [[Brazilian Women's Volleyball Superliga|Brazilian Superliga]] \u2013 [[File:Simple cup icon.svg|16px]] Champion, with [[Minas T\u00eanis Clube (women's volleyball)|Minas]]\n* 2007\u201308 [[Italian Women's Volleyball League|Italian League]] \u2013 [[File:Simple cup icon.svg|16px]] Champion, with [[Robursport Volley Pesaro|Scavolini Pesaro]]\n* 2010\u201311 [[Brazilian Women's Volleyball Superliga|Brazilian Superliga]] \u2013 [[File:Simple cup icon.svg|16px]] Champion, with [[Rio de Janeiro V\u00f4lei Clube|Unilever V\u00f4lei]]\n* 2014\u201315 [[2014\u201315 Turkish Women's Volleyball League|Turkish League]] \u2013 [[File:Gorm silver cup.jpg|16px]] Runner-up, with [[Vak\u0131fbank Spor Kul\u00fcb\u00fc|Vak\u0131fbank Istanbul]]\n* 2015\u201316 [[2015\u201316 Turkish Women's Volleyball League|Turkish League]] \u2013 [[File:Simple cup icon.svg|16px]] Champion, with Vak\u0131fbank Istanbul\n* [[2012 Women's South American Volleyball Club Championship|2012 South American Club Championship]] \u2013 [[File:Simple cup icon.svg|16px]] Champion, with [[Osasco Voleibol Clube|Molico Osasco]]\n* [[2014 Women's South American Volleyball Club Championship|2014 South American Club Championship]] \u2013 [[File:Gorm silver cup.jpg|16px]] Runner-up, with Molico Osasco\n* [[2020 Women's South American Volleyball Club Championship|2020 South American Club Championship]] \u2013 [[File:Simple cup icon.svg|16px]] Champion, with [[Minas T\u00eanis Clube (women's volleyball)|Itamb\u00e9/Minas]]\n* [[2007\u201308 Women's CEV Cup|2007\u201308 CEV Cup]] \u2013 [